t effect, since its upfront damage was only 250.  However, if you pull with EM, you tend to get a lot more agro, because by the time the pet engages the mob, the DoT has had time to do additional damage.<br>
<br>
Granted most of my experience above was before Verant introduced a lot of agro changes into the game (you know, when you used to be able to send in the pet and then sit down straight away, rather than having to wait for Jobober to gain sufficient agro first), so YMMV these days.  Also, a very very important thing to note is to NOT use EM or WoE when there is ANY possibility of getting adds and you have a chanter your the group, since DoTs will break mez every tick.<br>
 <p><b>Yarril</b><br>57th Mage on <i>Xev</i>
